Yes, I can help you extract the information from the text in a JSON object. Here is an example of how you could do this:
```
{
  "firstName": "",
  "lastName": "",
  "email": "michael.w@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "+1 555 123 4567",
  "address": "",
  "skills": [
    {
      "name": "Leadership",
      "value": "As a Project Manager, I lead cross-functional teams to deliver projects on time and within budget."
    },
    {
      "name": "Analytical Thinking",
      "value": "I handle project planning, resource allocation, and stakeholder communication."
    },
    {
      "name": "Project Management",
      "value": "As a Project Manager, I lead cross-functional teams to deliver projects on time and within budget."
    },
    {
      "name": "Data Analysis",
      "value": "I conduct data analysis, identify business trends, and provide insights to support decision-making."
    },
    {
      "name": "Stakeholder Communication",
      "value": "As a Project Manager, I handle project planning, resource allocation, and stakeholder communication."
    }
  ]
}
```
In this example, we have extracted the following information from the text:

* First name: Michael
* Last name: Williams
* Email address: michael.w@example.com
* Phone number: +1 555 123 4567
* Address: Villagetown
* Skills: Leadership, Analytical Thinking, Project Management, Data Analysis, Stakeholder Communication

Note that the skills are represented as an array of objects, where each object represents a skill and has a "name" and "value" property. The "value" property is the text from the original text that corresponds to the skill.
